.VL  
.LI "\*LXmNactivateCallback\*O"
Specifies a list of callbacks that is called
when the ArrowButton is activated.
To activate the button, press and release \*LBSelect\*O
while the pointer is inside
the ArrowButton widget.  Activating the ArrowButton
also disarms it.
The reason sent by this callback is \*LXmCR_ACTIVATE\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNarmCallback\*O"
Specifies a list of callbacks that is called
when the ArrowButton is armed.
To arm this widget, press \*LBSelect\*O
while the pointer is inside the ArrowButton.
The reason sent by this callback is \*LXmCR_ARM\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNarrowDirection\*O"
Sets the arrow direction.
The following are values for this resource:
.wH .rS 
.ML
.LI
\*LXmARROW_UP\*O.
.LI
\*LXmARROW_DOWN\*O.
.LI
\*LXmARROW_LEFT\*O.
.LI
\*LXmARROW_RIGHT\*O.
.LE 
.wH .rE
.LI "\*LXmNdisarmCallback\*O"
Specifies a list of callbacks that is called
when the ArrowButton is disarmed.
To disarm this widget, press and release
\*LBSelect\*O while the pointer is inside the ArrowButton.
The reason for this callback is \*LXmCR_DISARM\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNmultiClick\*O"
If a button click is followed by another button click within the time
span specified by the display's multi-click time, and this resource is
set to \*LXmMULTICLICK_DISCARD\*O, do not process the second click.
If this resource is set to \*LXmMULTICLICK_KEEP\*O, process the event
and increment \*Vclick_count\*O in the callback structure.
When the button is not in a menu, the default value is
\*LXmMULTICLICK_KEEP\*O.
.LE 
